table.caption: Table 184 – Additional entries specific to a file attachment annotation
head: Key
Type
Value
rows: (Required) The type of annotation that this dictionary describes; shallbe FileAttachment for a file attachment annotation.
(Required) The file associated with this annotation.

(Optional) The name of an icon that is used in displaying the annotation. Conforming readers shall provide predefined icon appearances for at least the following standard names:
GraphPushPin
PaperclipTag
Additional names may be supported as well. Default value: PushPin.
The annotation dictionary’s AP entry, if present, shall take precedence over the Name entry; see
Table 168
and
12.5.5, “Appearance Streams.”
